{
  "texts": [
    "It was worth noting that the included articles varied in how they reported the source of their data, with some specifying individual countries (e.g., UK, USA, Japan, Norway, Denmark), others referring to broader regions such as continents (e.g., North America, Europe, Australia), and some only indicating global recruitment.",
    "Healthcare was the most common real-world setting where AI-enabled cross-referenced extracted information across all included articles.",
    "The themes assigned were inspired by themes used in the included articles themselves and discussions among reviewers and authors.",
    "Additionally, the themes used were iteratively refined, ensuring that themes were accurately captured and aligned with the context provided in the articles.",
    "Importantly, when reviewing, we discovered that the included articles did not consistently or clearly distinguish between actual, perceived, planned, or suggested RAI practices."
  ]
}